poilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=163>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ambidexterity</span><hr size=1> Hmm... Gholam, you are saying that in the timespan that you had autoattack on, your Ragebringer (delay 25) provided 54% of the hits, while your offhand (delay 24) provided 46%? That sounds like about 82% dual wield chance to me. A bit higher than I thought it would be, but not 90%.<br>
<br>
Could you please show the calculations you used to show a 90% success rate?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Just in case someone asks me to provide the same, here is how I figured the rate to be about 82 percent using the numbers given. Since haste and double attack (as far as I know) effects both main and offhand the same way at high levels, I didn't include them in the calculations.<br>
<br>
Have autoattack on for, say, 6000 units of time. A Ragebringer with delay 25 would then have had a chance to swing 240 times. His hammer would with 100% dual wield success have had a chance to swing 250 times. Since his hammer swung only about (46/54)=85% as many times as his Ragebringer did, that would put it at about 204 swing-chances instead of 250, for a dual wield success percentage of about 82.<br>
<br>
If you chose another length of time, or included haste/double attack, you could alter the size of these two numbers (240 and 250), but not their relation to eachother. The number 204 was calculated from seeing how many times his offhand swung in relation to his mainhand, so it would scale along with the others. The relation between the 204 and the 250 was what gave me the result of 82%<br>
<br>
This took longer to write down than I spent on figuring it out, so if I did some error, feel free to correct it. For the best results, I hope misses were included in the calculation, but it shouldn't make any big difference unless your piercing skill varies alot from your 1hb. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqutsemnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutsemnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/24/02 3:22:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=164>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ambidexterity</span><hr size=1> well regardless in a time x the 24 del weapon will number swings 104% of the 25 del weapon.<br>
