 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sobal>Sobal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/02 6:28:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=169>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The way to go</span><hr size=1> This imho is the way to go:<br>
<br>
General Archetypes <br>
Run 1 (1)<br>
Run 2 (1)<br>
Run 3 (1)<br>
Regen 1 (1)<br>
Regen 2 (1)<br>
Regen 3 (1)<br>
Ok thats 6 points, you can move on.<br>
<br>
Melee Archetypes <br>
Combat Fury 1 (2)<br>
Combat Fury 2 (4)<br>
Combat Fury 3 (6)<br>
Thats 12 more points, your a Veteran now and can spend points on any skill you wish.<br>
<br>
Rogue Archetypes <br>
Ambidexterity (9)<br>
Chaotic Stab (6)<br>
Head back to melee archetypes and do them all with the exception of Fear Resistance and Finishing blow.<br>
<br>
After all that it really doesn't matter too much what you do.<br>
<br>
Anyways, thats my take on things. It's all good, no matter what order you follow.<br>
<br>
-Sobal<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
