 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelandileldaron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elandil Eldaron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/02 11:46:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=170>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The way to go</span><hr size=1> Hello,<br>
can someone give some significant statitics about critics and ambidextry on you dmg output.<br>
<br>
How much critic 3 improves your dmg output ?<br>
<br>
How much ambidextry improves your dmg output ?<br>
<br>
Just want a percentage from people who already have those skills. Parser and log analyser should help.<br>
<br>
Let's say you've doing 10K on Vindic, now how much you do in this fight with critic 3. And how much you do since you have ambidextry too.<br>
<br>
I ask questions cause i wanna know if it really improves dmg output significantly (i guess ambidextry do of course).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sobal>Sobal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/02 3:57:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=171>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The way to go</span><hr size=1> With crit 3 you land a critical hit on 7% of your landed attacks, including backstabs. Crits are 170% normal landed damage, I'll let you do the math on that one. <br>
<br>
As for Ambidex, there is some debate as to exactly how much bonus this skill adds to your DPS. It's somewhere around 4% added offhand DPS imo.<br>
<br>
What it all comes down to imo, is what increases DPS at all? Well, Combat Fury (crits), Ambidexterity (increased duel wield), and Chaotic stab (min damage front backstabs) are it.<br>
<br>
Regardless of what the DPS % increase is, training these skills is the best you can do to increase your combat damage output.<br>
<br>
Do what rogues do best, ALOT of damage.<br>
<br>
-Sobal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelcekindredsouls.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KelceKindredsouls</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/26/02 5:47:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=172>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The way to go</span><hr size=1> Would have to disagree with spending more than 2 points on Combat Fury, when you could put those points into ND1, 2 &amp; 3 (10% more base hitpoints sounds nifty).<br>
