With the weapons i hold, i already do a lot of damages, but the fact is, it's good to do a lot of damages but you better stay alive during a fight, a dead rogue means no damage at all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So i might maybe put critic 1 for the simple fact that landing a critic while Duelist on a backstab can do much on a target that you need to drop quick.<br>
<br>
But i think i will go on natural durability to increase significantly my HP.<br>
<br>
I think mostly aa pt depends of what you do in the game, for me i think i need more Hp than doing a bit more dmg, cause i do a lot of raids with many targets AE Sontalak, Keeper, etc...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sobal>Sobal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/02 4:16:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=174>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The way to go</span><hr size=1> Unbuffed, Natural Durability 3, takes me from 3111hp's to 3422hp's. (unbuffed sta is 204) Thats about 300hp's. An extra 300 hp's certainly helps soak up those aoe's, but I think doing the extra damage is more beneficial to the raid. I'm not saying natural dura isn't a great skill, i'm just an advocate of doing the dps skills first. <br>
<br>
Imo for rogues, dps &gt; hp's &gt; resists &gt; ac<br>
<br>
The nice thing about these aaxps skills is you are receiving a % increase to your dps. It doesn't matter if your still wielding Ragebringer or it's sitting in your bank, that percentage increase will carry over to every new weapon you get.<br>
<br>
Once again, all this is just my personal opinion. No matter what order you train skills in you're maximizing your effectiveness. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhuricrazyshorty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Huri Crazyshorty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/02 1:01:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=175>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The way to go</span><hr size=1> Escape has saved my Bacon MORE times then I care to comment.<br>
